    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fabulous beasts of composite form in Buddhist and other Japanese and Chinese art; in typical examples, they have the head of a dragon, body and legs of a stag or horse, tail of an ox or lion, single horn on the forehead, and parti-colored or scaly body.</Note_Text>
